'''斯科特·阿特拉斯'''（Scott William Atlas，{{bd|1955年|7月5日||}}）<ref>{{Cite web|title=Scott W. Atlas (Atlas, Scott W., 1955-)|url=http://onlinebooks.library.upenn.edu/webbin/book/lookupname?key=Atlas,%20Scott%20W.,%201955-|accessdate=August 31, 2020|work=onlinebooks.library.upenn.edu|archive-date=2020-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102112926/http://onlinebooks.library.upenn.edu/webbin/book/lookupname?key=Atlas,%20Scott%20W.,%201955-|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Resume|url=https://docs.house.gov/meetings/IF/IF14/20191210/110313/HHRG-116-IF14-Wstate-AtlasS-20191210-SD001.pdf|accessdate=2020-12-01|date=September 1, 2019|format=PDF|work=docs.house.gov|archive-date=2021-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316050957/https://docs.house.gov/meetings/IF/IF14/20191210/110313/HHRG-116-IF14-Wstate-AtlasS-20191210-SD001.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>是美国一名神经放射学教授、政治评论员和医疗保健政策顾问。他同時也是保守派智库[[胡佛研究所|胡佛研究所]]的高级研究员<ref name="Hoover">{{cite web|title=Scott W. Atlas—Hoover Institution Biography|url=https://www.hoover.org/profiles/scott-w-atlas|publisher=Hoover Institution|access-date=2020-12-01|archive-date=2021-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210322190333/http://www.hoover.org/profiles/scott-w-atlas|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。

2020年8月，阿特拉斯被美國總統[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]任命為[[白宫冠状病毒工作组|白宫冠状病毒工作组]]顾问。期間阿特拉斯传播[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情相關錯誤資訊|2019冠狀病毒病疫情相關錯誤資訊]]<ref name="AlbaLee">{{Cite web|title=Atlas on the outs with coronavirus task force but still pushing Trump's pandemic claims|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/atlas-outs-coronavirus-task-force-still-pushing-trump-s-pandemic-n1248258|author=Monica Alba & Carol E. Lee|publisher=NBC News|quote=Atlas, has not attended White House task force meetings in person since late September, according to two administration officials, as he continues to spread misinformation about the worsening health crisis. ... The growing split between Atlas and task force leaders came after the group's leading medical experts — Dr. Deborah Birx and Dr. Anthony Fauci — indicated that they did not appreciate Atlas’ controversial input or contributions in the Situation Room gatherings. "That was done in deference to Fauci and Birx because they basically said they will not work with him," a senior administration official said about the adviser's absence at the meetings.|access-date=2020-12-01|archive-date=2021-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121232459/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/atlas-outs-coronavirus-task-force-still-pushing-trump-s-pandemic-n1248258|dead-url=no}}</ref>，例如聲稱[[口罩|戴口罩]]和[[保持社交距離|保持社交距離]]对阻止[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情|2019冠狀病毒病疫情]]擴散沒有效果<ref>{{Cite news|date=2020|title=Trump’s den of dissent: Inside the White House task force as coronavirus surges|work=The Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-den-of-dissent-inside-the-white-house-task-force-as-coronavirus-surges/2020/10/19/7ff8ee6a-0a6e-11eb-859b-f9c27abe638d_story.html|accessdate=2020-12-01|archive-date=2020-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025205233/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-den-of-dissent-inside-the-white-house-task-force-as-coronavirus-surges/2020/10/19/7ff8ee6a-0a6e-11eb-859b-f9c27abe638d_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="Costa">{{Cite news|author=Abutaleb|first=Yasmeen|author2=Rucker|first2=Phillip|last3=Dawsey|first3=Josh|last4=Costa|first4=Robert|date=October 19, 2020|title=Trump’s den of dissent: Inside the White House task force as coronavirus surges|location=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-den-of-dissent-inside-the-white-house-task-force-as-coronavirus-surges/2020/10/19/7ff8ee6a-0a6e-11eb-859b-f9c27abe638d_story.html|accessdate=October 19, 2020|archive-date=2020-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025205233/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-den-of-dissent-inside-the-white-house-task-force-as-coronavirus-surges/2020/10/19/7ff8ee6a-0a6e-11eb-859b-f9c27abe638d_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="Stolberg">{{Cite news|author=Stolberg|first=Sheryl Gay|author2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|last3=Weiland|first3=Noah|date=October 19, 2020|title=Trump Calls Fauci ‘a Disaster’ and Shrugs Off Virus as Infections Soar|location=New York Times|url=https://nyti.ms/3jf8tvK|accessdate=October 19, 2020}}</ref> <ref name="Dawsey">{{Cite news|author=Dawsey|first=Josh|author2=Abutaleb|first2=Yasmeen|date=October 31, 2020|title=‘A whole lot of hurt’: Fauci warns of covid-19 surge, offers blunt assessment of Trump’s response|location=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/fauci-covid-winter-forecast/2020/10/31/e3970eb0-1b8b-11eb-bb35-2dcfdab0a345_story.html|accessdate=October 31, 2020|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226145253/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/fauci-covid-winter-forecast/2020/10/31/e3970eb0-1b8b-11eb-bb35-2dcfdab0a345_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="abc1">{{Cite web|title=Former Stanford colleagues warn Dr. Scott Atlas fosters 'falsehoods and misrepresentations of science'|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/stanford-colleagues-warn-dr-scott-atlas-fosters-falsehoods/story?id=72926212|accessdate=September 12, 2020|author=Bruggeman|first=Lucien|publisher=[[ABC新聞|ABC新聞]]|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120122756/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/stanford-colleagues-warn-dr-scott-atlas-fosters-falsehoods/story?id=72926212|archivedate=November 20, 2020}}</ref>。此外阿特拉斯在[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情|2019冠狀病毒病疫情]]期间還鼓勵年輕人接觸並感染[[嚴重急性呼吸系統綜合症冠狀病毒2型|嚴重急性呼吸系統綜合症冠狀病毒2型]]以產生[[群体免疫|群体免疫]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=美疾控中心主任私下谈话曝光：特朗普新冠顾问所说的都是假的|url=https://www.sohu.com/a/421642295_260616|accessdate=|author=澎湃新聞|date=|format=|publisher=|language=}}</ref><ref>{{link-en|Tucker Carlson Tonight}} (June 29, 2020). "Mixed messages: Corona deaths level off as cases surge". Interview with Scott Atlas. Fox News Channel. Quote: "We like the fact that there's a lot of cases in low-risk populations because that's exactly how we're going to get herd immunity—population immunity—when low-risk people with no significant problem handling this virus, which is basically 99% of people, uh, get this, they become immune and they block the pathways of connectivity to contagiousness of older, sicker people."</ref>、主張因疫情暫時關閉的学校和企业應迅速重新开放、認為美國各州不应该實行[[2019冠状病毒病检测|病毒全民检测]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Atlas push to 'slow the testing down' tracks with dramatic decline in one key state|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/29/politics/atlas-desantis-testing-covid-florida/index.html|accessdate=2020-10-29|author=CNN|first=John Avlon, Michael Warren and Brandon Miller|work=CNN|archive-date=2021-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321103501/https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/29/politics/atlas-desantis-testing-covid-florida/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，并呼籲美國人民抵制美國各州为防止[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情|2019冠狀病毒病疫情]]擴散而采取的居家令等限制措施<ref>{{Cite web|title=美白宫疫情顾问阿特拉斯辞职 曾支持“群体免疫”|url=http://news.xmnn.cn/xmnn/2020/12/01/100817838.shtml|accessdate=|author=中国新闻网|date=|format=|publisher=|language=}}</ref><ref name="LeBlanc">{{Cite news|author=LeBlanc|first=Paul|author2=Diamond|first2=Jeremy|date=November 15, 2020|title=Trump coronavirus adviser Scott Atlas urges Michigan to 'rise up' against new Covid-19 measures|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/15/politics/scott-atlas-coronavirus-michigan/index.html|location=[[有线电视新闻网|有线电视新闻网]]|accessdate=November 15, 2020|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314104238/https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/15/politics/scott-atlas-coronavirus-michigan/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2020年11月30日，阿特拉斯辞去[[白宫冠状病毒工作组|白宫冠状病毒工作组]]顾问一職<ref name="Resigns">Kaitlan Collins, Jim Acosta and Devan Cole, [https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/30/politics/scott-atlas-resigns-trump-administration-coronavirus-task-force/index.html Dr. Scott Atlas resigns from Trump administration] {{Wayback|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/30/politics/scott-atlas-resigns-trump-administration-coronavirus-task-force/index.html |date=20210729235758 }}, CNN (November 30, 2020).</ref>。

